column2: MIDDLE OF BASIN- INTEGRATED WATER COLUMN

The weather was dry and sunny.  It has been dry and sunny the past several days.  The water is very brown looking.  No life in the water where I was sampling.  Very little wildlife activity;  observed a Great Blue Heron and a sea gull.  A TP sample was collected 3 feet under water.  Sample taken to WalCoMet.

Lake looked brown in color- water a little clearer- and water was much colder.  Approximately 40 sea gulls floating on the water.  No other wildlife noticed on or near the water.  on North shore a beaver had gone up on shore to cut some Aspen branches.  The same hole is monitored- but the water level is always 5.5 feet- even when the feeder streams are flooding.
WDNR Rachel Sabre assisted.  Water body # 794200.  Phosphate sample was collected and sent to State Department of Hygiene.  Lake water was turbid- had a SW wind at about 5 mph.
Weather was cloudy and calm.  Lake Comus continues to be dirty looking with no vegetation growing in the water.

Tony Vidas assisted me with Lake monitoring.  We observed a Osprey carrying a fish to a nest on top of a large light pole in a near by park.  Lake had a greenish brown appearance.  It started to rain lightly while we were doing monitoring.

Tony Vidas assisted in collecting data.  Water was very brown- but the D.O. content was about normal.  D.O. very low about 1 1/2 miles upstream by Dam Road- 2.17 mg/l D.O.  A lot of crap jumping in lake.
